{"slug": "ward", "root": "ward", "category": "act", "gloss": "a protective magical guard", "definition": "A ward is a protective magical guard — a boundary or charm that keeps harm out. To ward is to defend by such means.", "history": "*Ward* is Old English *weardian*, 'to guard, watch' (Proto-Germanic *wardōn*); French borrowed the same Germanic root back as *guard*, making the two a doublet split by the Channel. A magical ward is protective magic in its oldest, plainest form. Magic made *Ward* an evergreen keyword in 2020 — a tax an opponent must pay to target the warded permanent — the ancient shielding charm rendered as a rule.", "def_sources": [{"label": "Etymonline, s.v. ward", "where": "Etymology reference"}, {"label": "the corpus", "where": "Corpus"}], "commentary": null, "commentary_sources": [], "is_keyword": true, "etymology": {"lang": "Old English", "origin": "Old English weardian 'to guard, watch' (Proto-Germanic *wardōn)", "first": "before 900", "note": "Guard is the same word borrowed back through French — a Germanic/Romance doublet. Warden, wardrobe, and toward all share it; now an MTG keyword too.", "hook": "'Guard' and 'ward' are the same word, split by the Channel."}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 22, "oracle_total": 339, "in_flavor_cards": 22, "in_oracle_cards": 322, "name_match_count": 27, "by_variant": {"ward": 349, "wards": 12}, "first_year": 1994, "colors": {"G": 102, "U": 136, "W": 96, "R": 60, "B": 70, "C": 26}, "by_year": {"1994": 1, "1995": 5, "1996": 1, "1997": 2, "1999": 1, "2001": 1, "2003": 1, "2005": 1, "2006": 1, "2007": 2, "2008": 2, "2010": 1, "2012": 2, "2013": 3, "2014": 1, "2015": 1, "2016": 2, "2017": 1, "2018": 5, "2019": 1, "2020": 5, "2021": 29, "2022": 60, "2023": 65, "2024": 113, "2025": 31, "2026": 33}}, "cards": [{"